It took almost a year for doctors to find the ideal combination of drugs, thanks to which he completely stopped having seizures. At the age of five, doctors stopped his medication, and because the seizures did not return, his parents thought that Honza was healthy and began to lead him more into sports. He rode a bicycle, skied, played tennis and floorball, and spent his free time playing games with his sister and friends. At the age of eleven, however, he had another seizure and it all started again.
Doctors tried different combinations of drugs again, but this time nothing worked, seizures in the form of absences kept recurring. Since Honza always lost sight of it during the attack, his parents were terrified that he would get it during sports and get injured. Gradually, Honza stopped riding his bike and exchanged downhill skis for cross-country skiing and snowboarding. Although the sport caused him a seizure from time to time, he never gave it up completely. He even fulfilled his dream and finished the Spartan Race, but together with a friend who was always in sight to help him in case of emergency.
When Honza was 15 years old, his parents decided to try to change doctors and turned to experts at the University Hospital in Motol. After a series of examinations, local doctors decided that Honza was a candidate for surgery to remove a lesion from his brain - the source of epileptic seizures. &quot;I had to have 2 surgeries in a row, first the doctors operated into my brain probes that sensed his activity, then they could remove my bearing. It was a hell of a few weeks for me. I just had to lie down and hardly move, wires stuck out of my head that were connected to a computer, &quot;recalls Honza.
The operation was successful and the doctors removed a relatively large deposit. &quot;The first days after the operation it was very mentally demanding, Honza was apathetic, confused, sad and almost didn&#39;t speak. Unlike how normally he is alive and communicative, it was a scary change, but fortunately everything returned to normal after a few days,&quot; he describes. mother and adds: &quot;A month and a half after the operation he had 1 seizure, but according to doctors it happens. Since then he has been without seizures for 3 months.&quot;
This school year, Honza will be graduating, in addition to sports, he enjoys languages and has started working with Company E, with which he travels around schools to discuss epilepsy. Honza is not yet fully engaged in sports activities, he is starting to return to sports gradually. &quot;I&#39;m learning how to play sports properly, how to breathe well so that I don&#39;t expose my body to sudden stress, which is quite a problem with my competitive nature,&quot; explains Honza.
This year, therefore, they will not yet actively participate in the traditional EPPI boating triathlon, where patients with epilepsy and healthy athletes meet and which takes place this weekend on September 28, 2019 at Veselská pískovna. But maybe next year.
XXX Lutz can buy a competitor Kika, the authority allowed. But it has a catch
&quot;The Office for the Protection of Competition has authorized the merger of competitors - XLCEE-Holding GmbH on the one hand, and Kika Nábytek and Lambda Properties Czechia on the other, subject to the fulfillment of structural commitments set in favor of maintaining effective competition,&quot; said Martin Švanda, spokesman for the Office.
In addition to the XXX Lutz chain, XLCEE-Holding owns Möbelix stores. If the Kika chain were to be swallowed up, it would occupy too much of the Czech furniture and accessories market. Therefore, he has to sell part of the company he is buying.
XLCEE-Holding also buys Kika branches in other countries where the chain operates, ie in Hungary, Slovakia and Romania. There, too, the transaction must be authorized by the antitrust authorities. XXX Lutz announced the purchase of 22 foreign branches of the Kika chain from the Signa holding in May. Signa took over the bankrupt Kika last year for a symbolic price.
The Kika chain entered the Czech market in 2005 and is number two after the Swedish company IKEA. Before it was taken over by the Austrian company Signa, it belonged to the South African company Steinhoff International Holdings from 2013. She faced problems when she discovered discrepancies in her accounting. Kika has nine stores in the Czech Republic.
XXX Lutz has been operating in the Czech Republic since 2010. In addition to IKEA, Sconto, Jysk and Asko-Nábytek and Kika, it is one of the largest furniture retailers on the domestic market. The Möbelix brand has the same owner. Following the acquisition of Kika&#39;s foreign branches, XXX Lutz will operate more than 300 department stores in 12 countries. According to the company&#39;s website, its annual turnover is 4.4 billion euros (about 114 billion CZK).
